data.enText: a thin object with a sharp point, especially a pointed piece of metal, wood, etc.
a row of iron spikes on a wall

data.chText: 她的头发一缕一缕地翘着。
data.enText: Her hair stood up in spikes.
a metal point attached to the sole of a sports shoe to prevent you from slipping while running
shoes fitted with these metal spikes , used for running
a pair of spikes
a long pointed group of flowers that grow together on a single stem
a sudden large increase in sth
a spike in oil prices
to push a sharp piece of metal, wood, etc. into sb/sth; to injure sth on a sharp point

data.chText: 在…中偷偷掺入（烈酒、毒药或毒品）
data.enText: to add alcohol, poison or a drug to sb's drink or food without them knowing

data.chText: 他给了她一杯偷偷放了镇静剂的饮料。
data.enText: He gave her a drink spiked with tranquillizers.
Her words were spiked with malice.

data.chText: 拒绝发表；阻止…传播；阻挠
data.enText: to reject sth that a person has written or said; to prevent sth from happening or being made public

data.chText: 因担心被提起诉讼，报社未发表那篇文章。
data.enText: The article was spiked for fear of legal action against the newspaper.

data.enText: spike sb's guns
to spoil the plans of an opponent

tr: sports equipment consisting of a sharp point on the sole of a shoe worn by athletes

example: they used spikes to fasten the rails to a railroad tie

tr: any holding device consisting of a rigid, sharp-pointed object
example: the spike pierced the receipts and held them in order

tr: a long, thin sharp-pointed implement (wood or metal)
example: one of the spikes impaled him

tr: a sharp-pointed projection along the top of a fence or wall (or a dinosaur)
each of the sharp points on the soles of athletic shoes to prevent slipping (or the shoes themselves)
example: the second baseman sharpened his spikes before every game
golfers' spikes damage the putting greens

tr: a very high narrow heel on women's shoes
a transient variation in voltage or current
a sharp rise followed by a sharp decline
example: the seismograph showed a sharp spike in response to the temblor

tr: (botany) an indeterminate inflorescence bearing sessile flowers on an unbranched axis
fruiting spike of a cereal plant especially corn
bring forth a spike or spikes
example: my hyacinths and orchids are spiking now

tr: pierce with a sharp stake or point
example: impale a shrimp on a skewer

value.def: A spike is a long piece of metal with a sharp point.

example.tran: 顶端装有铁刺的 15 英尺高的墙

example.ex: Yellowing receipts had been impaled on a metal spike.
example.tran: 发黄的收据被穿在一根金属扦上。

value.def: Any long pointed object can be referred to as a spike .

example.ex: Her hair stood out in spikes.
example.tran: 她的头发一簇簇竖立着。

value.def: If there is a spike in the price, volume, or amount of something, the price, volume, or amount of it suddenly increases.

example.ex: Although you'd think business would have boomed during the war, there was only a small spike in interest.
example.tran: 人们会认为战争期间生意会很红火，但实际上利息只有小幅上升。

value.def: Spikes are a pair of sports shoes with pointed pieces of metal attached to the soles. They help runners' feet to grip the ground when they are running.
If your drink is spiked, someone has added alcohol or drugs to it without telling you.

example.ex: They wondered whether their drinks had been spiked.
example.tran: 他们有些疑惑自己的饮料里是否被偷偷搀了烈性酒。
被偷偷加了镇静剂的饮料

value.tran: 偷偷往(饮料中)搀烈性酒(或毒品)
